            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EUnbelief%20is%20dangerous%2C%20regardless%20of%20who%20you%20are.%20Zechariah%2C%20a%20member%20of%20the%20priestly%20tribe%2C%20was%20standing%20in%20the%20Holy%20Place%20offering%20incense%20before%20God%20when%20an%20angel%20of%20the%20Lord%20brought%20him%20a%20message.%20Because%20he%20refused%20to%20believe%20the%20message%20and%20questioned%20the%20power%20of%20God%2C%20Zechariah%20was%20struck%20dumb.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EAnother%20example%20of%20unbelief%20is%20found%20in%20Numbers%2020%3A11-12%2C%20which%20tells%20how%20Moses'%20and%20Aaron's%20lack%20of%20trust%20in%20God%20led%20them%20to%20act%20rashly.%20They%20struck%20the%20rock%20twice%20instead%20of%20merely%20speaking%20to%20it%20as%20God%20had%20instructed.%20This%20simple%20act%20of%20unbelief%20disqualified%20them%20from%20their%20long-awaited%20entrance%20into%20the%20Promised%20Land.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EGod%20does%20not%20exempt%20His%20leaders%20from%20judgment%20if%20they%20fail%20to%20walk%20before%20Him%20in%20the%20purity%20of%20faith.%20He%20%22doesn't%20show%20partiality%22%20(Acts%2010%3A34)%20and%20equally%20dispenses%20judgment%20on%20all%20who%20refuse%20to%20believe.%20His%20judgment%20can%20be%20swift%20and%20stern%2C%20as%20when%20Uzzah%20was%20struck%20dead%20for%20steadying%20the%20ark%20of%20the%20covenant%20after%20the%20oxen%20stumbled%20(1%20Chronicles%2013%3A9-10).%20In%20another%20instance%2C%20%22Aaron's%20sons%20Nadab%20and%20Abihu%20put%20coals%20of%20fire%20in%20their%20incense%20burners%20and%20sprinkled%20incense%20over%20it%22%20(Leviticus%2010%3A1)%20and%20were%20immediately%20burned%20alive%20by%20the%20fire%20of%20God.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EGod%20is%20awesome%20in%20His%20holiness%20and%20will%20not%20be%20disregarded.%20%20Let's%20serve%20Him%20with%20the%20proper%20respect%20and%20awe%2C%20%22for%20our%20God%20is%20a%20consuming%20fire%22%20(Hebrews%2012%3A29).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Numbers.19:1-20:29",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3ENumbers%2019%3A1-20%3A29%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_19_1%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3ENumbers%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Water%20of%20Purification%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20said%20to%20Moses%20and%20Aaron%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_19_2%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BHere%20is%20another%20legal%20requirement%20commanded%20by%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%3A%20Tell%20the%20people%20of%20Israel%20to%20bring%20you%20a%20red%20heifer%2C%20a%20perfect%20animal%20that%20has%20no%20defects%20and%20has%20never%20been%20yoked%20to%20a%20plow.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_19_3%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EGive%20it%20to%20Eleazar%20the%20priest%2C%20and%20it%20will%20be%20taken%20outside%20the%20camp%20and%20slaughtered%20in%20his%20presence.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_19_4%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EEleazar%20will%20take%20some%20of%20its%20blood%20on%20his%20finger%20and%20sprinkle%20it%20seven%20times%20toward%20the%20front%20of%20the%20Tabernacle.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E19%3A4%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20Tent%20of%20Meeting.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_19_5%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EAs%20Eleazar%20watches%2C%20the%20heifer%20must%20be%20burned%26%23x2014%3Bits%20hide%2C%20meat%2C%20blood%2C%20and%20dung.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_19_6%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EEleazar%20the%20priest%20must%20then%20take%20a%20stick%20of%20cedar%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E19%3A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Ejuniper.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20a%20hyssop%20branch%2C%20and%20some%20scarlet%20yarn%20and%20throw%20them%20into%20the%20fire%20where%20the%20heifer%20is%20burning.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_19_7%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BThen%20the%20priest%20must%20wash%20his%20clothes%20and%20bathe%20himself%20in%20water.%20Afterward%20he%20may%20return%20to%20the%20camp%2C%20though%20he%20will%20remain%20ceremonially%20unclean%20until%20evening.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_19_8%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20man%20who%20burns%20the%20animal%20must%20also%20wash%20his%20clothes%20and%20bathe%20himself%20in%20water%2C%20and%20he%2C%20too%2C%20will%20remain%20unclean%20until%20evening.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_19_9%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20someone%20who%20is%20ceremonially%20clean%20will%20gather%20up%20the%20ashes%20of%20the%20heifer%20and%20deposit%20them%20in%20a%20purified%20place%20outside%20the%20camp.%20They%20will%20be%20kept%20there%20for%20the%20community%20of%20Israel%20to%20use%20in%20the%20water%20for%20the%20purification%20ceremony.%20This%20ceremony%20is%20performed%20for%20the%20removal%20of%20sin.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_19_10%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20man%20who%20gathers%20up%20the%20ashes%20of%20the%20heifer%20must%20also%20wash%20his%20clothes%2C%20and%20he%20will%20remain%20ceremonially%20unclean%20until%20evening.%20This%20is%20a%20permanent%20law%20for%20the%20people%20of%20Israel%20and%20any%20foreigners%20who%20live%20among%20them.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_19_11%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BAll%20those%20who%20touch%20a%20dead%20human%20body%20will%20be%20ceremonially%20unclean%20for%20seven%20days.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_19_12%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20must%20purify%20themselves%20on%20the%20third%20and%20seventh%20days%20with%20the%20water%20of%20purification%3B%20then%20they%20will%20be%20purified.%20But%20if%20they%20do%20not%20do%20this%20on%20the%20third%20and%20seventh%20days%2C%20they%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20unclean%20even%20after%20the%20seventh%20day.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_19_13%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EAll%20those%20who%20touch%20a%20dead%20body%20and%20do%20not%20purify%20themselves%20in%20the%20proper%20way%20defile%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Tabernacle%2C%20and%20they%20will%20be%20cut%20off%20from%20the%20community%20of%20Israel.%20Since%20the%20water%20of%20purification%20was%20not%20sprinkled%20on%20them%2C%20their%20defilement%20continues.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_19_14%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BThis%20is%20the%20ritual%20law%20that%20applies%20when%20someone%20dies%20inside%20a%20tent%3A%20All%20those%20who%20enter%20that%20tent%20and%20those%20who%20were%20inside%20when%20the%20death%20occurred%20will%20be%20ceremonially%20unclean%20for%20seven%20days.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_19_15%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EAny%20open%20container%20in%20the%20tent%20that%20was%20not%20covered%20with%20a%20lid%20is%20also%20defiled.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_19_16%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20if%20someone%20in%20an%20open%20field%20touches%20the%20corpse%20of%20someone%20who%20was%20killed%20with%20a%20sword%20or%20who%20died%20a%20natural%20death%2C%20or%20if%20someone%20touches%20a%20human%20bone%20or%20a%20grave%2C%20that%20person%20will%20be%20defiled%20for%20seven%20days.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_19_17%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BTo%20remove%20the%20defilement%2C%20put%20some%20of%20the%20ashes%20from%20the%20burnt%20purification%20offering%20in%20a%20jar%2C%20and%20pour%20fresh%20water%20over%20them.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_19_18%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20someone%20who%20is%20ceremonially%20clean%20must%20take%20a%20hyssop%20branch%20and%20dip%20it%20into%20the%20water.%20That%20person%20must%20sprinkle%20the%20water%20on%20the%20tent%2C%20on%20all%20the%20furnishings%20in%20the%20tent%2C%20and%20on%20the%20people%20who%20were%20in%20the%20tent%3B%20also%20on%20the%20person%20who%20touched%20a%20human%20bone%2C%20or%20touched%20someone%20who%20was%20killed%20or%20who%20died%20naturally%2C%20or%20touched%20a%20grave.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_19_19%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EOn%20the%20third%20and%20seventh%20days%20the%20person%20who%20is%20ceremonially%20clean%20must%20sprinkle%20the%20water%20on%20those%20who%20are%20defiled.%20Then%20on%20the%20seventh%20day%20the%20people%20being%20cleansed%20must%20wash%20their%20clothes%20and%20bathe%20themselves%2C%20and%20that%20evening%20they%20will%20be%20cleansed%20of%20their%20defilement.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_19_20%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BBut%20those%20who%20become%20defiled%20and%20do%20not%20purify%20themselves%20will%20be%20cut%20off%20from%20the%20community%2C%20for%20they%20have%20defiled%20the%20sanctuary%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20Since%20the%20water%20of%20purification%20has%20not%20been%20sprinkled%20on%20them%2C%20they%20remain%20defiled.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_19_21%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20is%20a%20permanent%20law%20for%20the%20people.%20Those%20who%20sprinkle%20the%20water%20of%20purification%20must%20afterward%20wash%20their%20clothes%2C%20and%20anyone%20who%20then%20touches%20the%20water%20used%20for%20purification%20will%20remain%20defiled%20until%20evening.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_19_22%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EAnything%20and%20anyone%20that%20a%20defiled%20person%20touches%20will%20be%20ceremonially%20unclean%20until%20evening.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_20_1%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3ENumbers%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EMoses%20Strikes%20the%20Rock%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EIn%20the%20first%20month%20of%20the%20year%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E20%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20The%20first%20month%20of%20the%20ancient%20Hebrew%20lunar%20calendar%20usually%20occurs%20within%20the%20months%20of%20March%20and%20April.%20The%20number%20of%20years%20since%20leaving%20Egypt%20is%20not%20specified.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20the%20whole%20community%20of%20Israel%20arrived%20in%20the%20wilderness%20of%20Zin%20and%20camped%20at%20Kadesh.%20While%20they%20were%20there%2C%20Miriam%20died%20and%20was%20buried.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_20_2%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EThere%20was%20no%20water%20for%20the%20people%20to%20drink%20at%20that%20place%2C%20so%20they%20rebelled%20against%20Moses%20and%20Aaron.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_20_3%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20people%20blamed%20Moses%20and%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BIf%20only%20we%20had%20died%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20presence%20with%20our%20brothers!%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22numb_20_4%22%20bk%3D%22numb%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EWhy%20have%20you%20brought%20the%20congregation%20of%20the%20%